==English==

===Etymology===
Origin is uncertain but two theories [[predominate]].
# The early English migrants had pale complexions like [[pomegranate]]s.
# An [[acronym]] of "Prisoner of His Majesty", which was stamped on the uniforms of [[transported]] prisoners.  However, many [[historian]]s [[dispute]] this claim.

===Pronunciation===
Pom.ee

===Alternative spellings===
*[[pommy]]

===Noun===
#([[Colloquial]]) Australian term for an [[English]] [[immigrant]].

===Adjective=== 
#(''Colloquial'').  English.
#: ''His daughter has a Pommie boyfriend''.

